SIMPLE: em
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Em
<hw>'Em</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An obsolete or colloquial contraction of
the old form <xex>hem</xex>, them.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Em</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Em
<hw>Em</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>The
portion of a line formerly occupied by the letter <xex>m</xex>, then a
square type, used as a unit by which to measure the amount of printed
matter on a page; the square of the body of a type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Em-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Em-
<hw>Em-</hw>. <def>A prefix. See <er>En-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emacerate</ent>⟦br⟧
